post_text: BREAKING NEWS! We will be piloting a food sharing table at Hardwick Elementary School, Ruggles Lane Elementary School and Oakham Center School. The local Board of Health at each of the above schools have giving us permission for the food sharing tables. Students can leave certain foods they do not want from their school breakfast or school lunch (No food from home) & any student can take items off the table at no cost. This will help reduce food waste and help reduce student hunger. Quabbin Middle High school will again have their food sharing cooler for this upcoming school year. We are very excited to be able to implement food sharing tables.

Please take a moment to urge Congress to support School Food Modernization Act (S. 1949/H.R. 3444) to help school nutrition programs serve healthy food. Our schools need optimally functioning kitchen equipment to be able to feed children nutritious meals, and the School Food Modernization Act will expand schools’ access to modern kitchen equipment and infrastructure and strengthen workforce training.

Tell Congress to support the School Food Modernization Act! If you have already contacted your congressional representatives: THANK YOU! If you haven’t taken action, take action today! Click the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics Action Center at https://www.eatrightpro.org/action-center. It only takes a few minutes to send your message!
